class_name IslandMap
extends RefCounted

## The valley level as an ASCII map — the single source of truth for layout.
##
## Generated by tools/gen_valley.py (variant 1, "valley-1"); 192 wide x 48 tall.
## Terrain, props, and entity spawns all derive from it: level.gd paints terrain
## + collision, main.gd instantiates props/animals, encounter_manager.gd places
## enemies. Lives in a .gd const (not a .txt) because the Web export packs only
## Godot resources — a text file would silently vanish from browser builds.
##
## Legend (full table in docs/level-design.md). Families:
##   terrain   .grass  #path  Sspawn  D/Qfarm  ccobble  ~water  Bbridge  ggrape-arch
##   water-set O boat  k/@ capybara  a/l swimming duck/swan   (all keep water under)
##   buildings H Evan's stall  L library  A/G/J/E cottages  Y barn  W well
##   trees     T/t oak  4/5 birch  6/7 spruce  8/9 fruit
##   props     F/| fence  i/+ lamp  b bench  x chest  n sign  z windmill  s tent
##             0 campfire  1 camp-prop  2 hay  3 barrel  K scarecrow  = trough
##             % beehive  & berry  r rock  u stump  m mushroom  w/f flowers
##   cast      N villager  $ Ariana  C chicken  ^ rooster  d duck  U goose
##             R frog  j mouse  y butterfly  h horse  o/p/e cow/pig/sheep
##
## Design rules the art imposes (edge sheets have no 1-wide strip tiles):
##   - keep water/path/farm regions at least 2 tiles wide
##   - the preview renderer (tools/preview_map.py) validates violations to 0

